subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis . Tegmen lanceolated with a conspicuous yellowish-green venation, delineated, resembling a mined leaf in the costal vein, costal vein containing yellow spots (
Fig. 2
). Tympanic foramen green in both sides. Forceps-like cerci, denticulate in the distal portion. Subgenital plate long (mean 5.1 mm ), anterior margin deeply emarginated. Styles cylindrical.

